50|$|Kenaf Persian, Hibiscus cannabinus, is a {{plant in}} the Malvaceae family also called Deccan hemp and Java jute. Hibiscus cannabinus is in the genus Hibiscus and is native to {{southern}} Asia, though its exact origin is unknown. The name also applies to the fibre obtained from this plant. Kenaf {{is one of the}} <b>allied</b> <b>fibres</b> of jute and shows similar characteristics.|$|E
